Restart the application to complete the installation process.

nodes.title: Guide
widgets_values:
I've arranged this workflow to somewhat resemble the layout of Forge/A1111 UI, but its not exactly the same since that would make useful groups of nodes too far apart from one another to be convenient and use them efficiently.

The work flow has the following Layout from left to right:

TXT2IMG - IMG2IMG - TXT2VDO/IMG2VDO

Colour Codes:

Generation: Blue
Refiners: Purple
Modifiers: Red
Assets (Lora, embedding etc): Yellow
Utilities: Green

It is still a work in progress, I am adding new things all the time, since I'm relatively new to comfy and wanted to make something that resembles what I'm used to, its my hope that this will help other Forge/A1111 users have an easier time learning comfy.

If you don't know what a certain node does, I strongly recommend googling it and reading the explanations on github, usually the developers give some explanation as to what their nodes do and how to use them.

Make sure you have RGthree installed, its a fantastic node set that lets you right click and only run group nodes or nodes up to a certain point so you don't have to bypass everything else all the time.

I'd really appreciate it if you could upload some of your creations and/or give feedback on my civitai page.

Many Thanks
